description:
Located below Flatbush in south Brooklyn. Bright, spacious apartment on the 2nd floor. Key-less electronic locks. Conveniently located near transportation, shopping, dining, parks, playgrounds, and beaches. New to Airbnb, so if we've missed anything during your stay please don't hesitate to ask and we'll accommodate to the best of our abilities! Good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, and furry friends (pets).

I or someone else will be available at all times to help. Whatever a guest needs whether it be info, recommendations, new sheets, etc I'm more than happy to help...any way I can make your stay more enjoyable, just let me know!

Our neighborhood is very safe with a classic Brooklyn mix of commercial and residential. There are numerous stores/restaurants (all within walking distance) with everything you could need surrounding quiet, tree-lined residential streets. For more fun details (ASK ME)!

There are bus stops almost directly in front of the apartment and trains into Manhattan a short 10-minute bus ride away. 
Metered parking in front of our apartment and free street parking on the streets to the side and behind our place.

Bus: Q35, B41, B9 stops within a couple feet
Train: 2/5 (10 minutes away), B/Q (15 minutes away)
$2 Commuter vans run on Flatbush Ave and Utica Ave

1. We're located on a main street and there will be some noise. We also run a puppy store next door so don't be suprised if you hear some puppies barking!
2. We also have some neighbors who are musicians so free music can be heard some evenings.

hosts.about:
I live and travel extensively in China -- for sourcing and inspecting your products as well as designing your personal ideas to make your dreams and budget come true.

I have been to Shanghai, Beijing, Shangdong, Shundong, Nimbo, Guanzhou, Shenzhen, Guangdong, Hubei, Dali, Huazhou, Hong Kong, Xiamen, Changping, Dongguang, and more then 9 other provinces. 
I have inspected and visited more then 176+ factories during my 7 years in China. 
I speak level CET 1 Mandarin and have 3 full time translators who speak 4 languages.
If you like puppies, then this is your magical kingdom as I manage a puppy store  right next door...but i secretly love cats!  
I'm a Sci-Fi addict and in my spare time I design and create  new inventions to make the world a better place.
I attended landmark and a weekly meet of an all-male organization called Sterling Institute for Masculine Relationships with up to 300 attendees...
very powerful place to gain leadership skills and become a role model  for young men and ladies in our society --  

I will make  your stay with me fun, friendly, safe and as my guest, you will be taken care of.  
My motto is tattooed on my body...(have your dreams  but  make them  real )
有你的梦想,但让他们真正的

David and Lisa
